\begin_layout Standard
CKMR is a major advance in population ecology,
 and this paper provides a significant step towards fully leveraging this new method.
 We are the first to demonstrate how CKMR can be combined with IMR into a unified model.
 Our method improves precision in estimates of population size and demographic parameters compared to IMR alone.
 We provide an example of ICKMR study design,
 including model development,
 model checking,
 and design calculations,
 and show how simulated data can be used to evaluate different proposed survey designs.
 While we used walrus as a motivating example,
 we intend our work to provide a roadmap to other researchers considering ICKMR as a tool to estimate population parameters across a range of taxa.
